[{"location":"ref/#Reference","page":"Reference","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ref/#TinOpener.bootstrap","page":"Reference","title":"TinOpener.bootstrap","text":"bootstrap(x::DataFrame)\n\nBootstrap a DataFrame, i.e. sample its rows with replacement.\n\n\n\n\n\nbootstrap(x::GroupedDataFrame{DataFrame})\n\nBootstrap a GroupedDataFrame, i.e. separately call bootstrap on each of its subdataframes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ref/#TinOpener.bin_time","page":"Reference","title":"TinOpener.bin_time","text":"bin_time(x::DataFrame; time_variable = \"date\", bin_resolution = 10)\n\nBin the time variable in a DataFrame into bin_resolution equally spaced bins. Returns a BinnedCorpus.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ref/#TinOpener.categorical_to_proportion","page":"Reference","title":"TinOpener.categorical_to_proportion","text":"categorical_to_proportion(x::BinnedCorpus, variable, ref_level;\n    expand_missing = true, shuffle = false)\n\nTransform a categorical variable into its proportion, calculated per time bin.\n\nThe variable is first transformed into a vector of ones and zeroes; whenever the value coincides with ref_level, we replace the value with a one, otherwise we replace it with a zero. The proportion of ref_level per time bin is then calculated as the mean over this vector of ones and zeroes.\n\nThe output is a BinnedTimeSeries.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ref/#TinOpener.impute","page":"Reference","title":"TinOpener.impute","text":"impute(x::BinnedTimeSeries; nnsize = 2)\n\nCarry out nearest-neighbour imputation (with neighbourhood size nnsize) over a BinnedTimeSeries.\n\nReturn value is a BinnedTimeSeries with missing values replaced by imputed values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#TinOpener.jl","page":"Home","title":"TinOpener.jl","text":"(Image: )\n\nTinOpener is the Swiss army knife of the WWW-SArDEEn project at the University of Zurich.\n\nIts main features at the moment include:\n\nprocessing of historical corpora and datasets extracted therefrom\ntime series analysis\ncausality and complexity measures","category":"section"},{"location":"#Acknowledgement","page":"Home","title":"Acknowledgement","text":"Development of TinOpener.jl is funded by the Swiss National Science Foundation (SNSF).\n\nPicture of sardines courtesy of the Freshwater and Marine Image Bank, public domain (source).","category":"section"}]
